This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it deals with the interplay between the topology of complex networks and the robustness and scaling properties of a large-scale data centre. It could also belong to the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) as it explores the properties of different network topologies. Additionally, it could be classified under the sub-category of Systems and Control (cs.SY) as it deals with system-level performance metrics. It could also be classified under the sub-categories of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) as these areas are relevant to the study of large-scale data centres.
